Michael R. McCurdy

Michael R. McCurdy's civil litigation practice involves a broad range of substantive areas, including extensive litigation experience in state and federal courts; commercial and business matters; product and professional liability; employment; dram shop, wrongful death and catastrophic injury cases. In addition to having defended cases against their insureds, Mike is experienced in defending insurers in bad faith actions and is skilled in analyzing insurance coverage issues. He also is experienced in the use of alternative dispute resolution procedures to avoid formal litigation. View All 
Hide All 

Representative Experience
 

 Defended officers and directors in state and federal court litigation,  involving breach of fiduciary duty claims Analyzed insurance coverage disputes and represented insurers in bad faith and insurance coverage litigation Litigated commercial claims arising from myriad of disputes, including breach of contract, commercial leases and real estate Defended product liability claims involving a wide variety of products, and litigated tort liability claims, including wrongful death, catastrophic injury and premises liability claims Acted as outside general counsel for a medical device company serving domestic and international customers Represented defendants in federal bankruptcy court adversarial litigation Litigated claims involving complex trust agreements Represented individuals in complex, high-net-worth domestic relations matters, including business and personal practice valuations, trusts and parental responsibility  


Professional Affiliations
 

 American Bar Association American Law Firm Association   Editor, “International Client Seminar Course Book,” 1999   Colorado Bar Association Colorado Defense Lawyers Association Denver Bar Association Defense Research Institute (DRI), 1997 - 2011   Business Litigation Excess and Reinsurance Group    


Recognition
 

